{
  "texts": [
    "These are however challenging for CNNs, as discussed in [86].",
    "Signed distance functions [86] or simulations on coarse grids provide superior alternatives.",
    "For inverse problems, an initial forward simulation of an initial guess of the inverse field can be used to encode the desired boundary conditions [105,[108][109][110].",
    "Another possibility for CNNs is a decomposition of the domain.",
    "The mapping can be performed on the full domain [111], smaller subdomains [112], or even individual pixels [113]."
  ]
}